Patience is our friend here....

UP THE WOLVES 🧡🧡🧡

The link up #wwfc have with Grasshoppers is brilliant and could have saved us £30m (the emergence of Toti) and being able to send Jordao there for top flight competitive football is priceless, especially after his injury.

Which elite footballer will sign for #wwfc in January (in WC year) when (if Lage continues 3-4-3) RN and JM are first picks ( and have been available for 95% games since promotion). Don't get the Donck rage either...he's the same squad player he was 3 years ago.

On the pitch, the #wwfc squad is a good one...crikey, we've got to 8th in the PL without incurring too much debt / tightening our belts after the uefa ffp nonsense. There are obvious gaps in the squad when it's fully fit but we need to sign elite footballers...

Whether as fans we like it or not,  Fosun want #wwfc to be self sufficient and to do that our income streams need to increase so we can afford top players and regularly pay top transfer fees. That much is simple I think and why the alien concept of esports etc is developed.
